Rules
'F' means move one step forward
'L' means turn left (90 degrees)
'R' means turn right (90 degrees)
'B' means turn back (180 degrees) 
' ' is walkable space
'#' is a thorn bush (impassable)
'^', '<', 'v' or '>' îs the initial direction of unit that must flee the maze. 
You 'escape' if you reach the edge of the grid 

Explicit requirements
- Must return a list of minimum required moves to escape
- If the maze has no exit, return an empty array
- The grid will always be rectangular

Implicit requirements
- 'B' (Turn back) means turn 180 degrees. 
- You are placed randomly in the grid 
- Victory condition is if you reach either the first row i.e row[0] or the last row ie row[-1], or if in a given row you reach col[0] or col[-1] 
- Your starting position is where one of the ^ < v or > symbols are located in the grid, i.e the row and col index, and is necessary to check surroundings
- You have a position and a direction 
- If you go up a blind end, you should backtrack and delete moves from an array 

Examples
